                       "message":  "PROJECT-NAME-DISPLAY: show a .rge-project\u0027s manifest name, not its folder\n\nA .rge-project save source now displays its declared manifest `name`\n(rge_data::Project.name) in the window title + status bar, falling back to the\nproject folder name when the name is absent / unreadable / empty. Previously it\nalways showed the folder name.\n\nLean, additive, loader-free design (editor-shell takes no rge-data dep):\n- rge-scene-loader: + `read_project_name(path) -\u003e Option\u003cString\u003e` (additive;\n  reuses the crate\u0027s existing rge-data + ron deps). Returns None on any I/O /\n  parse failure so a bad manifest degrades to the folder fallback. World-free\n  (no scene load) — a one-shot Open/launch read, not a per-frame path.\n- SceneOpenHook: + defaulted `project_display_name(\u0026path) -\u003e Option\u003cString\u003e`\n  returning None, so the mock + all existing call sites compile unchanged; the\n  binary-owned loader hook overrides it.\n- SaveSource::Project(PathBuf) -\u003e Project { path, name: Option\u003cString\u003e }; the\n  name lives in the variant (no parallel EditorShell field). display_name()\n  prefers a present non-empty name, else the existing folder fallback.\n- Construction sites thread the name: in-app Ctrl+O via the hook\n  (open_request.rs), `--scene` launch via read_project_name (main.rs).\n\nload_scene_world_from_path\u0027s signature is untouched (it has ~14 callers) — the\nadditive read_project_name exists precisely to avoid that ripple.\n\nTests: read_project_name golden-loads \"simple-scene\" + None for a missing path;\ndisplay_name prefers the manifest name, falls back to folder when None/empty;\nstatus snapshot surfaces the name end-to-end. Existing project tests carry\nname: None.\n\n7 files, 0 Cargo.toml. Gate: VERIFY OK (7/7), 10/10 arch lints.\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 (1M context) \u003cnoreply@anthropic.com\u003e",
