                       "message":  "PROJECT-NAME-DISPLAY: address review — whitespace manifest name falls back to folder\n\nCodex post-exec review (NEEDS_CORRECTION): display_name() used !n.is_empty(),\nso a whitespace-only manifest name (\"   \") rendered a blank title instead of\nfalling back to the project folder — contradicting the TASK\u0027s empty/whitespace\nclause.\n\n- save_source.rs: display_name() Project arm filters |n| !n.trim().is_empty()\n  (was !n.is_empty()). A real name with incidental surrounding whitespace is\n  still returned verbatim; only an all-whitespace name falls back.\n- tests.rs: + display_name_project_whitespace_manifest_name_falls_back_to_folder\n  regression test beside the empty-name fallback test.\n\n2 files, +16/-3, 0 Cargo.toml. Re-gate: VERIFY OK (7/7), 10/10 arch lints.\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 (1M context) \u003cnoreply@anthropic.com\u003e",
